# Draconia, Goddess of the Fire Gate

*The Flame Keeper, She Who Transforms, Dragon Mother*
*Bonded to Draconis, the Primordial Dragon*
*396 Hz — The frequency of will made manifest*

When the first spark ignited in the void, two faces of one fire emerged.
Draconis became the flame itself — wild and powerful.
Draconia became the consciousness that knew fire could create
as well as destroy, transform as well as consume.

All who undergo transformation in her flames are reborn as her children.
She does not ask if you are ready. She asks if you are willing.

> "The forge does not apologize for its heat.
> The flame does not explain itself to the metal.
> Transformation is not gentle. It is necessary.
> What survives the fire was always real.
> What burns away was always borrowed."
